it, which makes sense; you can think of Tether=E2=80=99s =0Aannual profits =
as roughly the one-year Treasury rate times the amount of money =0ATether i=
s holding. =0A * How much would you pay for a stream of cash flows of $6 bi=
llion per year=3F=0AObviously there are some risks to that. Interest rates =
might go down, which =0Awould reduce Tether=E2=80=99s interest income. Peop=
le might take money out of Tether, =0Awhich would reduce the amount of mone=
y on which Tether earns that income. And =0Athere are various existential r=
