napse and were unable to determine which end-users rightfully should be abl=
e to withdraw their funds. As a result, they froze access to a portion of t=
he funds for an extended period while they attempted to determine ownership=
. According to the Trustee=E2=80=99s ninth status report as of September 1=
3, 2024, of the approximate $219 million aggregate funds held by Synapse=E2=
=80=99s partner banks in custodial =E2=80=9CFBO=E2=80=9D accounts, approxim=
ately $165 million (or roughly 75%) had been distributed to end users, with=
 $54 million, or approximately 25%, remaining to be distributed. =E2=80=A6<=
/p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Synapse essentially told the world that onl=
